Most Germans Oppose Waiving of Greek Debt, Emnid Poll Shows

-- B y   R a i n e r   B u e r g i n
-- 
2011-07-21T15:28:53Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-21/most-germans-oppose-waiving-of-greek-debt-emnid-poll-shows.html
Sixty-one percent of Germans are
opposed to granting Greece partial debt relief and 56 percent
believe the euro has brought them mainly disadvantages,  N24 
television said today, citing a poll it commissioned from Emnid
GmbH.  Sixty-two percent of respondents said  Chancellor Angela Merkel ’s management of the euro region’s sovereign-debt crisis
is “rather bad,” N24 said. It said the poll of around 1,000
people was conducted yesterday. No margin of error was given.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Rainer Buergin in Berlin at 
 rbuergin1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
James Hertling at   jhertling@bloomberg.net  